data.title: Eucalyptus camaldulensis Dehnh.
data.meta_description: The native range of this species is Australia. It is a tree and grows primarily in the desert or dry shrubland biome. It is used as animal food, a medicine and invertebrate food, has environmental uses and for fuel and food.
